    "summarizer": {
      "general_reader_takeaway": "This paper argues that a purely geometric effect in General Relativity\u2014arising from how matter clumps develop mathematical singularities\u2014can explain why the outer regions of galaxies rotate faster than visible matter alone would predict, without invoking dark matter. The review board found the underlying idea creative and potentially significant, but identified serious technical concerns. The paper defers all substantive derivations to a companion paper listed under a placeholder arXiv identifier (\"000000\"), making independent evaluation impossible, and a key mathematical step\u2014the choice of Bessel functions used to solve the core equation\u2014is disputed between reviewers and needs human expert verification.",
      "reviewer": "claude",
      "technical_takeaway": "The paper proposes that GR backreaction from action-level spacetime surgery at \"matter horizons\" (pre-caustic surfaces motivated by the Raychaudhuri equation) generates a geometric effective EMT contribution. Through a Poisson equation for the backreaction potential\u2014argued to reduce to a Modified Bessel equation\u2014the paper claims flat galaxy rotation curves and MOND-like 1/r force scaling emerge naturally. Two issues dominate the adversarial cross-review: (1) reference 23 (Umeh:2026pm, arXiv ID \"000000\") is inaccessible, deferring every non-trivial derivation\u2014equations of motion (12), effective EMT (13\u201314), propagation equation (20), junction conditions, and viscosity terms\u2014outside the paper; (2) a disputed mathematical error in eq. (22)\u2013(23): gemini and claude argue the 3D spherical Laplacian (d\u00b2\u03a6/dr\u00b2 + (2/r)d\u03a6/dr) should yield spherical Bessel solutions k\u2080 ~ e^{\u2212\u03b2r}/r (Keplerian decline), not cylindrical I\u2080/K\u2080, making flat rotation curves an artifact of the wrong function class; codex disputes this after inspecting the actual PDF, reporting a g = r\u00b2d\u03a6/dr substitution yielding I\u2081/K\u2081 in a transformed variable. The departure from Israel-Darmois junction conditions in favor of conformal Killing equations is flagged as unjustified by all three reviewers."
    }
